                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On October 15, 1950, President Truman, General MacArthur, and a number of other
                    officials met at Wake Island. Their conversations touched at several points on
                    issues related to United States policy toward Japan. For a compilation by
                    General Bradley of certain notes kept by the conferees from Washington, see <ref
                        target="frus1950v07#pg_948">volume VII, page 948</ref>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
